did.unittitle: News and Information Services (University of Michigan) photograph series D (faculty and staff portraits) 1946-2006, 1950-1990
did.abstract: The University of Michigan News and Information Services functions as the university's media relations office. It disseminates information and images about university programs, research, events, and faculty and staff activities. This series of News and Information Services photographs is comprised of portraits of more than 4,000 individual faculty and staff members spanning the years 1946-2006 (bulk 1950-1990).

repository.corpname: Bentley Historical Library, University of Michigan

acqinfo.p: University of Michigan News and Information Services (donor no. 285) periodically deposits its photographs with the library. 285

accruals.p: No further additions to Series D, faculty portraits are expected.

accessrestrict.p: The Series "D" faculty portraits are open without restriction.

userestrict.p: Copyright is held by the regents of the University of Michigan. A credit line must be given to News and Information Services, University of Michigan if a photograph is used in a publication.

prefercite.p: [item], folder, box, News and Information Services (University of Michigan) photograph series D (faculty and staff portraits), Bentley Historical Library, University of Michigan

bioghist.p: The University of Michigan News and Information Services is responsible for preparing press releases about university activities, providing photographs and film of university functions and scholarly announcements to the various news media, and publishing and distributing the University Record and Michigan Today.

News and Information Services has undergone several name and organizational changes throughout its history. Beginning in 1897, the university had a department of information services that performed many of the functions of a press office. In 1930, following the installation of President Alexander G. Ruthven, the university created a News Dissemination Service (often called the University of Michigan News Service). Over the ensuing decades the name of the organization has changed from News Service to Information Services, and finally to News and Information Services. The organizational home of the unit has also changed as it moved from an independent unit to part of the Bureau of Alumni Relations, and later part of the Office of University Relations. It currently is part of the Vice President for Communications.

scopecontent.p: This series, commonly known as "Series D" is part of the News and Information Services photographs collection, which consists of several other series often based on format such as the size of the negatives (4x5 or 35mm) or content (general campus photography or aerial photographs). Series D consists of black and white 4x5 inch negatives and 1-1/4 x 2-1/4 inch prints and negatives of faculty and staff (and some student) portraits alphabetically arranged.

A comprehensive index for the entire series was created in 2007. It replaces what had been a partial index covering less than half of the content (two additions were received after the initial index was prepared). Based on information supplied on the original envelopes, the listing includes faculty/staff name, department or unit (when provided) and date(s) of the portrait. Bentley Library negative numbers are included (if applicable).
